subSubSection.paragraph:
C. muttensis
sp. n. only occurs in the Mutt glacial stream where larvae are apparently confined to the lotic part of springs and the rhithral (crystalline to calcareous water). Emergence from July to early August. Associated species found in the same locality include: 
C. laminatus
Brundin, 1947; 
C. cf. longivirgatus
Stur & Spies, 2011; 
C. suecicus
(Kieffer, 1916); 
Heleniella helvetica
.
